<div>
    <h3 id = "english">What is 'Privacy Criteria Method'?</h3>
    <p class = "textao">
    Data from software applications often reveal a large amount of personal information andcan be used for purposes other than those originally intended. Disclosure of thisinformation in an unregulated way raises privacy concerns. Thus, the literature reports theneed for systematic approaches to specifying privacy requirements. In addition, it is well-known that agile software development (ASD) has been increasingly adopted in theindustry as it can minimize the challenges related to requirements changes through shortiterations and active stakeholders. However, recent empirical works have shown thatrequirements approach for ASD still neglects non-functional requirements (NFRs). To helpto address this issue, we developed PCM Tool that supports the Privacy Criteria Method(PCM), an approach designed to guide software engineers in the specification of privacyrequirements in agile software development.</p>
